-- Government Bonds Slide After India's Central Bank Raises Interest Rates
-- Anil Varma
-- 2010-07-05T03:41:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/bonds-slide-after-india-s-central-bank-unexpectedly-raises-interest-rates.html

          
          
             India’s 10-year bonds fell after the
central bank increased benchmark interest rates on July 2 for
the third time this year. The yield on the benchmark 7.8 percent
note due 2020 climbed eight basis points to 7.64 percent as of
9:09 a.m. in Mumbai, according to the central bank’s trading
system. The price dropped 0.59, or 59 paise per 100 rupee face
amount, to 101.06.  
          
          


  


        